{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":703,"text":"This is how war starts."},{"time":3515,"text":"One day you're living your ordinary life,"},{"time":6781,"text":"you're planning to go to a party,"},{"time":9297,"text":"you're taking your children to school,"},{"time":11681,"text":"you're making a dentist appointment."},{"time":14394,"text":"The next thing, the telephones go out,"},{"time":18020,"text":"the TVs go out, there's armed men on the street,"},{"time":21957,"text":"there's roadblocks."},{"time":24273,"text":"Your life as you know it goes into suspended animation."},{"time":28750,"text":"It stops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30955,"text":"I'm going to steal a story from a friend of mine,"},{"time":33513,"text":"a Bosnian friend, about what happened to her,"},{"time":36491,"text":"because I think it will illustrate for you exactly what it feels like."},{"time":40868,"text":"She was walking to work one day in April, 1992,"},{"time":44962,"text":"in a miniskirt and high heels. She worked in a bank."},{"time":48110,"text":"She was a young mother. She was someone who liked to party."},{"time":51634,"text":"Great person."},{"time":53468,"text":"And suddenly she sees a tank"},{"time":56775,"text":"ambling down the main road of Sarajevo"},{"time":59981,"text":"knocking everything out of its path."},{"time":63533,"text":"She thinks she's dreaming, but she's not."},{"time":67564,"text":"And she runs as any of us would have done"},{"time":70309,"text":"and takes cover, and she hides behind a trash bin,"},{"time":74326,"text":"in her high heels and her miniskirt."},{"time":76925,"text":"And as she's hiding there, she's feeling ridiculous,"},{"time":81144,"text":"but she's seeing this tank go by with soldiers"},{"time":83840,"text":"and people all over the place and chaos"},{"time":86200,"text":"and she thinks, \"I feel like Alice in Wonderland"},{"time":90827,"text":"going down the rabbit hole,"},{"time":93162,"text":"down, down, down into chaos,"},{"time":96230,"text":"and my life will never be the same again.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":101631,"text":"A few weeks later, my friend was in a crowd of people"},{"time":105418,"text":"pushing with her infant son in her arms"},{"time":110368,"text":"to give him to a stranger on a bus,"},{"time":112904,"text":"which was one of the last buses leaving Sarajevo"},{"time":115928,"text":"to take children out so they could be safe."},{"time":119093,"text":"And she remembers struggling with her mother to the front,"},{"time":123203,"text":"crowds and crowds of people, \"Take my child! Take my child!\""},{"time":126629,"text":"and passing her son to someone through a window."},{"time":132682,"text":"And she didn't see him for years."},{"time":135550,"text":"The siege went on for three and a half years,"},{"time":139269,"text":"and it was a siege without water,"},{"time":141558,"text":"without power, without electricity, without heat, without food,"},{"time":146847,"text":"in the middle of Europe, in the middle of the 20th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152202,"text":"I had the honor of being one of those reporters"},{"time":156004,"text":"that lived through that siege,"},{"time":158423,"text":"and I say I have the honor and the privilege of being there"},{"time":161461,"text":"because it's taught me everything,"},{"time":163651,"text":"not just about being a reporter, but about being a human being."},{"time":167780,"text":"I learned about compassion."},{"time":170135,"text":"I learned about ordinary people who could be heroes."},{"time":173946,"text":"I learned about sharing. I learned about camaraderie."},{"time":178317,"text":"Most of all, I learned about love."},{"time":181228,"text":"Even in the midst of terrible destruction and death and chaos,"},{"time":186507,"text":"I learned how ordinary people could help their neighbors,"},{"time":189643,"text":"share food, raise their children,"},{"time":192287,"text":"drag someone who's being sniped at from the middle of the road"},{"time":195539,"text":"even though you yourself were endangering your life,"},{"time":198396,"text":"helping people get into taxis who were injured"},{"time":201647,"text":"to try to take them to hospitals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204268,"text":"I learned so much about myself."},{"time":207487,"text":"Martha Gellhorn, who's one of my heroes, once said,"},{"time":210512,"text":"\"You can only love one war. The rest is responsibility.\""},{"time":215710,"text":"I went on to cover many, many, many wars after that,"},{"time":219246,"text":"so many that I lost count,"},{"time":221875,"text":"but there was nothing like Sarajevo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224958,"text":"Last April, I went back to a very strange --"},{"time":228913,"text":"what I called a deranged high school reunion."},{"time":232687,"text":"What it was, was the 20th anniversary of the siege,"},{"time":237030,"text":"the beginning of the siege of Sarajevo,"},{"time":239502,"text":"and I don't like the word \"anniversary,\" because it sounds like a party,"},{"time":243942,"text":"and this was not a party."},{"time":245345,"text":"It was a very somber gathering of the reporters"},{"time":249333,"text":"that worked there during the war, humanitarian aid workers,"},{"time":252724,"text":"and of course the brave and courageous people of Sarajevo themselves."},{"time":257193,"text":"And the thing that struck me the most,"},{"time":259612,"text":"that broke my heart,"},{"time":261353,"text":"was walking down the main street of Sarajevo,"},{"time":263523,"text":"where my friend Aida saw the tank coming 20 years ago,"},{"time":267598,"text":"and in that road were more than 12,000 red chairs,"},{"time":274295,"text":"empty,"},{"time":275921,"text":"and every single one of them symbolized"},{"time":278190,"text":"a person who had died during the siege,"},{"time":281907,"text":"just in Sarajevo, not in all of Bosnia,"},{"time":286194,"text":"and it stretched from one end of the city"},{"time":288781,"text":"to a large part of it,"},{"time":291055,"text":"and the saddest for me were the tiny little chairs"},{"time":294558,"text":"for the children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297414,"text":"I now cover Syria,"},{"time":300541,"text":"and I started reporting it because I believed that"},{"time":303731,"text":"it needs to be done."},{"time":305987,"text":"I believe a story there has to be told."},{"time":308992,"text":"I see, again, a template of the war in Bosnia."},{"time":312962,"text":"And when I first arrived in Damascus,"},{"time":315191,"text":"I saw this strange moment where people"},{"time":317593,"text":"didn't seem to believe that war was going to descend,"},{"time":321153,"text":"and it was exactly the same in Bosnia"},{"time":323088,"text":"and nearly every other country I've seen where war comes."},{"time":325902,"text":"People don't want to believe it's coming,"},{"time":328445,"text":"so they don't leave, they don't leave before they can."},{"time":331912,"text":"They don't get their money out."},{"time":333582,"text":"They stay because you want to stay in your home."},{"time":337477,"text":"And then war and chaos descend."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341516,"text":"Rwanda is a place that haunts me a lot."},{"time":345319,"text":"In 1994, I briefly left Sarajevo to go report the genocide in Rwanda."},{"time":351473,"text":"Between April and August, 1994,"},{"time":356322,"text":"one million people were slaughtered."},{"time":360523,"text":"Now if those 12,000 chairs freaked me out"},{"time":365750,"text":"with the sheer number,"},{"time":367822,"text":"I want you just for a second to think of a million people."},{"time":371453,"text":"And to give you some example, I remember"},{"time":373990,"text":"standing and looking down a road as far as I could see,"},{"time":379071,"text":"at least a mile, and there were bodies piled twice my height"},{"time":385160,"text":"of the dead."},{"time":386884,"text":"And that was just a small percentage of the dead."},{"time":390219,"text":"And there were mothers holding their children"},{"time":392188,"text":"who had been caught in their last death throes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395529,"text":"So we learn a lot from war,"},{"time":398859,"text":"and I mention Rwanda"},{"time":401211,"text":"because it is one place, like South Africa,"},{"time":405329,"text":"where nearly 20 years on, there is healing."},{"time":409311,"text":"Fifty-six percent of the parliamentarians are women,"},{"time":412779,"text":"which is fantastic,"},{"time":415231,"text":"and there's also within the national constitution now,"},{"time":419257,"text":"you're actually not allowed to say Hutu or Tutsi."},{"time":422430,"text":"You're not allowed to identify anyone by ethnicity,"},{"time":426299,"text":"which is, of course, what started the slaughter in the first place."},{"time":430845,"text":"And an aid worker friend of mine told me the most beautiful story,"},{"time":433952,"text":"or I find it beautiful."},{"time":435435,"text":"There was a group of children, mixed Hutus and Tutsis,"},{"time":440352,"text":"and a group of women who were adopting them,"},{"time":443066,"text":"and they lined up and one was just given to the next."},{"time":447000,"text":"There was no kind of compensation for, you're a Tutsi,"},{"time":450166,"text":"you're a Hutu, you might have killed my mother,"},{"time":453081,"text":"you might have killed my father."},{"time":454927,"text":"They were just brought together in this kind of reconciliation,"},{"time":460233,"text":"and I find this remarkable."},{"time":463817,"text":"So when people ask me how I continue to cover war,"},{"time":466659,"text":"and why I continue to do it,"},{"time":468871,"text":"this is why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470340,"text":"When I go back to Syria, next week in fact,"},{"time":473731,"text":"what I see is incredibly heroic people,"},{"time":477692,"text":"some of them fighting for democracy,"},{"time":479965,"text":"for things we take for granted every single day."},{"time":483982,"text":"And that's pretty much why I do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487220,"text":"In 2004, I had a little baby boy,"},{"time":491688,"text":"and I call him my miracle child,"},{"time":494883,"text":"because after seeing so much death"},{"time":497929,"text":"and destruction and chaos and darkness in my life,"},{"time":502106,"text":"this ray of hope was born."},{"time":505965,"text":"And I called him Luca, which means \"The bringer of light,\""},{"time":510162,"text":"because he does bring light to my life."},{"time":515085,"text":"But I'm talking about him because when he was four months old,"},{"time":518536,"text":"my foreign editor forced me to go back to Baghdad"},{"time":523208,"text":"where I had been reporting all throughout the Saddam regime"},{"time":526540,"text":"and during the fall of Baghdad and afterwards,"},{"time":529419,"text":"and I remember getting on the plane in tears,"},{"time":532513,"text":"crying to be separated from my son,"},{"time":535499,"text":"and while I was there,"},{"time":537732,"text":"a quite famous Iraqi politician who was a friend of mine"},{"time":540467,"text":"said to me, \"What are you doing here?"},{"time":542941,"text":"Why aren't you home with Luca?\""},{"time":544782,"text":"And I said, \"Well, I have to see.\" It was 2004"},{"time":548567,"text":"which was the beginning of the incredibly bloody time in Iraq,"},{"time":552954,"text":"\"I have to see, I have to see what is happening here."},{"time":556194,"text":"I have to report it.\""},{"time":557059,"text":"And he said, \"Go home,"},{"time":560623,"text":"because if you miss his first tooth,"},{"time":563909,"text":"if you miss his first step, you'll never forgive yourself."},{"time":566907,"text":"But there will always be another war.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":570770,"text":"And there, sadly, will always be wars."},{"time":575111,"text":"And I am deluding myself if I think, as a journalist,"},{"time":578965,"text":"as a reporter, as a writer,"},{"time":580731,"text":"what I do can stop them. I can't."},{"time":585569,"text":"I'm not Kofi Annan. He can't stop a war."},{"time":588116,"text":"He tried to negotiate Syria and couldn't do it."},{"time":591093,"text":"I'm not a U.N. conflict resolution person."},{"time":595089,"text":"I'm not even a humanitarian aid doctor,"},{"time":597372,"text":"and I can't tell you the times of how helpless I've felt"},{"time":600198,"text":"to have people dying in front of me, and I couldn't save them."},{"time":603469,"text":"All I am is a witness."},{"time":607304,"text":"My role is to bring a voice to people who are voiceless."},{"time":612358,"text":"A colleague of mine described it as to shine a light"},{"time":615591,"text":"in the darkest corners of the world."},{"time":618353,"text":"And that's what I try to do."},{"time":621000,"text":"I'm not always successful,"},{"time":624036,"text":"and sometimes it's incredibly frustrating,"},{"time":626577,"text":"because you feel like you're writing into a void,"},{"time":628783,"text":"or you feel like no one cares."},{"time":631112,"text":"Who cares about Syria? Who cares about Bosnia?"},{"time":633361,"text":"Who cares about the Congo,"},{"time":635374,"text":"the Ivory Coast, Liberia, Sierra Leone,"},{"time":637648,"text":"all of these strings of places that"},{"time":639763,"text":"I will remember for the rest of my life?"},{"time":643736,"text":"But my métier is to bear witness"},{"time":646989,"text":"and that is the crux, the heart of the matter,"},{"time":650171,"text":"for us reporters who do this."},{"time":652712,"text":"And all I can really do is hope,"},{"time":656303,"text":"not to policymakers or politicians,"},{"time":658911,"text":"because as much as I'd like to have faith"},{"time":661308,"text":"that they read my words and do something,"},{"time":663773,"text":"I don't delude myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666933,"text":"But what I do hope is that if you remember anything I said"},{"time":671150,"text":"or any of my stories tomorrow morning over breakfast,"},{"time":674703,"text":"if you can remember the story of Sarajevo,"},{"time":677385,"text":"or the story of Rwanda,"},{"time":680876,"text":"then I've done my job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683449,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685487,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}